item.title: Actual First Post
item.description: This is my first post! library(reticulate) ## Warning: package 'reticulate' was built under R version 4.0.3 print("Here's an R chunk!") ## [1] "Here's an R chunk!" In python, you can create data structures called ‘dictionaries’. Dictionaries allowed you to store a ‘key’ and pair it with one or more ‘values’. Although unordered, it is possible to extract a value or values associated with a key. In the following python code chunk, I have provided an example of a dictionary.
